1
00:01:55,031 --> 00:01:57,522
Hi, everybody.
This is your cousin Brucie. Whoa!

2
00:01:57,600 --> 00:02:01,661
Our summer romances are in full bloom,
and everybody's in love!

3
00:02:01,738 --> 00:02:04,832
So cousins, here's a great song
from the Four Seasons.

4
00:02:12,148 --> 00:02:14,912
That was the summer of 1963...

5
00:02:14,984 --> 00:02:18,545
when everybody called me ""Baby""
and it didn't occur to me to mind.

6
00:02:27,497 --> 00:02:29,624
That was before
President Kennedy was shot...

7
00:02:29,699 --> 00:02:31,667
before the Beatles came...

8
00:02:31,734 --> 00:02:33,827
when I couldn't wait
to join the Peace Corps...

9
00:02:33,903 --> 00:02:37,805
and I thought I'd never
find a guy as great as my dad.

10
00:02:47,283 --> 00:02:49,843
That was the summer
we went to Kellerman's.

11
00:03:09,072 --> 00:03:12,064
Ping-Pong in the west arcade,
softball in the east diamond.

12
00:03:12,141 --> 00:03:14,405
All you Sandy Koufaxes,
get out there!

13
00:03:14,477 --> 00:03:16,945
Complimentary dance lessons
in the gazebo.

14
00:03:17,013 --> 00:03:19,641
Oh, my God.
Look at that!

15
00:03:19,716 --> 00:03:23,846
Mom, I should've brought the coral
shoes. You said I was taking too much.

16
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:26,548
Well, sweetheart,
you brought ten pairs.

17
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:29,114
But the coral shoes
matched that dress.

18
00:03:29,192 --> 00:03:30,853
This is not a tragedy.

19
00:03:30,927 --> 00:03:35,387
A tragedy is three men trapped in a mine
or police dogs used in Birmingham.

20
00:03:35,465 --> 00:03:37,660
Monks burning themselves
in protest.

21
00:03:37,734 --> 00:03:39,133
Butt out, Baby.

22
00:03:39,202 --> 00:03:42,933
Okay, we got horseshoes
on the south lawn in 15 minutes!

23
00:03:43,006 --> 00:03:45,975
We've got splish-splash
the water class down by the lake.

24
00:03:46,042 --> 00:03:49,637
We have the still life art class.
We got volleyball and croquet.

25
00:03:49,712 --> 00:03:52,272
And for you older folks,
we got sacks!

26
00:03:55,018 --> 00:03:55,051
Doc!

27
00:03:55,051 --> 00:03:56,382
Doc!

28
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:58,348
Max!

29
00:03:58,421 --> 00:04:03,188
Doc, after all these years
I finally got you up on my mountain.

30
00:04:04,060 --> 00:04:05,493
How's the blood pressure?

31
00:04:05,561 --> 00:04:07,495
I want you girls to know...

32
00:04:07,563 --> 00:04:10,964
if it were not for this man,
I'd be standing here dead.

33
00:04:11,801 --> 00:04:14,235
- Billy, get the bags.
- Right away, Doc.

34
00:04:14,304 --> 00:04:17,535
I kept the best cabin
for you and your beautiful girls.

35
00:04:21,277 --> 00:04:23,404
Hey, thanks a lot.

36
00:04:23,479 --> 00:04:25,208
You want a job here?

37
00:04:25,281 --> 00:04:28,409
There's a merengue class in
the gazebo in the next few minutes.

38
00:04:28,484 --> 00:04:31,214
The greatest teacher.
Used to be a Rockette.

39
00:04:31,287 --> 00:04:35,246
It's his first real vacation
in six years, Max. Take it easy.

40
00:04:35,325 --> 00:04:38,226
Three weeks here,
it'll feel like a year.

41
00:04:38,294 --> 00:04:41,855
One, two, three, four! Stomp
those grapes and stomp some more!

42
00:04:41,931 --> 00:04:46,061
One, two, three, four!
Listen to the music!

43
00:04:46,135 --> 00:04:47,568
Sorry.

44
00:04:47,637 --> 00:04:49,400
Move your caboose
and shake it loose!

45
00:04:49,472 --> 00:04:53,272
One, two, three, four!
Start the train!

46
00:04:57,780 --> 00:05:00,578
Come on, men!
Follow me into a round robin!

47
00:05:01,617 --> 00:05:03,881
Ladies, the inner circle!

48
00:05:13,896 --> 00:05:15,488
Come on, ladies!

49
00:05:15,565 --> 00:05:20,025
God wouldn't have given you maracas
if he didn't want you to shake them!

50
00:05:24,340 --> 00:05:27,104
Okay now, ladies,
when I say ""stop""...

51
00:05:27,176 --> 00:05:30,168
you're gonna find
the man of your dreams.

52
00:05:31,247 --> 00:05:32,509
Stop!

53
00:05:34,217 --> 00:05:38,313
Remember, he's the boss on
the dance floor, if nowhere else.

54
00:05:47,196 --> 00:05:50,461
Mom, Dad, I'm going up
to the main house to look around.

55
00:06:28,071 --> 00:06:30,801
There are two kinds of help here.

56
00:06:30,873 --> 00:06:33,034
You waiters are
all college guys...

57
00:06:33,109 --> 00:06:37,011
and I went to Harvard
and Yale to hire you.

58
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:40,049
And why did I do that? Why?

59
00:06:41,484 --> 00:06:44,282
I shouldn't have to remind you.
This is a family place.

60
00:06:44,353 --> 00:06:48,153
That means you keep your fingers out
of the water, hair out of the soup...

61
00:06:48,224 --> 00:06:50,385
and show the goddamn
daughters a good time.

62
00:06:51,227 --> 00:06:52,660
All the daughters.

63
00:06:54,163 --> 00:06:56,324
Even the dogs.

64
00:06:56,399 --> 00:06:59,163
Schlepp 'em out to the terrace,
show 'em the stars.

65
00:06:59,235 --> 00:07:01,533
- Romance 'em any way you want.
- Got that, guys?

66
00:07:01,604 --> 00:07:03,572
Hey, hold it!
Hold it.

67
00:07:05,475 --> 00:07:09,104
Well, if it isn't
the entertainment staff.

68
00:07:09,178 --> 00:07:11,510
Listen, wise ass,
you got your own rules.

69
00:07:11,581 --> 00:07:13,742
Dance with the daughters.
Teach 'em the mambo...

70
00:07:13,816 --> 00:07:16,478
the cha-cha,
anything they pay for.

71
00:07:16,552 --> 00:07:18,144
That's it.

72
00:07:18,221 --> 00:07:20,382
That's where it ends.

73
00:07:20,456 --> 00:07:24,119
No funny business, no conversations,
and keep you hands off!

74
00:07:27,063 --> 00:07:30,726
It's the same at all these places. Some
ass in the woods, but no conversation.

75
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,734
Watch it, Rodriguez.

76
00:07:34,937 --> 00:07:38,873
Can you keep that straight, Johnny?
What you can't lay your hands on?

77
00:07:43,279 --> 00:07:47,079
Just put your pickle on everybody's
plate, and leave the hard stuff to me.

78
00:07:53,756 --> 00:07:56,316
Sit down and I'll
get you some wine.

79
00:07:57,193 --> 00:07:58,717
Thank you, Max.

80
00:08:01,998 --> 00:08:03,761
This is Dr. and Mrs. Houseman.

81
00:08:03,833 --> 00:08:07,894
Baby, Lisa, this is your waiter,
Robbie Gould.

82
00:08:07,970 --> 00:08:10,666
Yale medical school.

83
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:14,642
These people are my special guests.
Give them anything they want.

84
00:08:14,710 --> 00:08:16,644
- Enjoy.
- Thanks, Max.

85
00:08:21,350 --> 00:08:25,582
Look at all this leftover food. Are
there still starving children in Europe?

86
00:08:25,655 --> 00:08:28,385
- Try Southeast Asia, Ma.
- Right.

87
00:08:28,457 --> 00:08:31,051
Robbie, Baby wants to send
her leftover pot roast...

88
00:08:31,127 --> 00:08:34,255
to Southeast Asia,
so anything you don't finish, wrap up.

89
00:08:35,164 --> 00:08:37,792
Max, our Baby's gonna
change the world.

90
00:08:37,867 --> 00:08:41,234
- And what are you gonna do, Missy?
- Lisa's gonna decorate it.

91
00:08:41,304 --> 00:08:43,397
She already does.

92
00:08:45,408 --> 00:08:49,310
Doc, I want you to meet someone.
My grandson Neil.

93
00:08:49,378 --> 00:08:51,812
Goes to the Cornell School
of Hotel Management.

94
00:08:51,881 --> 00:08:54,145
Baby's starting
Mount Holyoke in the fall.

95
00:08:55,151 --> 00:08:56,846
Oh, great.

96
00:09:05,528 --> 00:09:07,120
Are you going to major in English?

97
00:09:07,196 --> 00:09:10,654
No. Economics of
underdeveloped countries.

98
00:09:10,733 --> 00:09:14,134
- I'm going into the Peace Corps.
- After the final show...

99
00:09:14,203 --> 00:09:18,003
I'm going to Mississippi with
a couple of busboys, freedom ride.

100
00:09:37,426 --> 00:09:39,986
This is our own Tito Suarez.

101
00:10:27,243 --> 00:10:29,677
Mambo!
Yeah! Come on!

102
00:10:36,919 --> 00:10:39,046
Who's that?

103
00:10:39,121 --> 00:10:41,555
Oh, them.
They're the dance people.

104
00:10:41,624 --> 00:10:44,593
They're here to keep
the guests happy.

105
00:11:07,283 --> 00:11:11,413
They shouldn't show off with each other.
That's not gonna sell lessons.

106
00:12:28,364 --> 00:12:30,889
- Hi, kids. Having fun?
- Yeah.

107
00:12:30,966 --> 00:12:34,834
Actually, I've gotta excuse myself.
I'm in charge of the games tonight.

108
00:12:34,904 --> 00:12:37,634
Would you like to help me
get things started?

109
00:12:37,706 --> 00:12:39,401
Sure she would.

110
00:12:46,749 --> 00:12:50,845
This'll only hurt for a minute.
You've got Blue Cross, right?

111
00:13:00,229 --> 00:13:02,697
Was that good for you?

112
00:13:02,765 --> 00:13:06,394
And for being such a good sport,
here you go!

113
00:13:12,174 --> 00:13:14,870
I finally met a girl
exactly like my mother.

114
00:13:14,944 --> 00:13:18,004
Dresses like her, acts like her.
So I brought her home.

115
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:20,014
My father doesn't like her!

116
00:13:21,784 --> 00:13:23,615
Go figure.

117
00:14:12,568 --> 00:14:15,196
- Hi.
- How'd you get here?

118
00:14:15,271 --> 00:14:16,863
- I was taking a walk.
- Go back.

119
00:14:16,939 --> 00:14:18,930
Let me help you.
What's up there?

120
00:14:19,008 --> 00:14:20,942
No guests allowed.
House rules.

121
00:14:21,010 --> 00:14:25,470
Why don't you go back to the playhouse?
I saw you dancing with little boss man.

122
00:14:30,319 --> 00:14:32,253
Can you keep a secret?

123
00:14:34,557 --> 00:14:37,117
Your parents would kill you.

124
00:14:37,192 --> 00:14:39,126
Max would kill me.

125
00:15:32,214 --> 00:15:34,546
Where'd they learn to do that?

126
00:15:34,617 --> 00:15:36,482
Where?

127
00:15:36,552 --> 00:15:39,544
I don't know. Kids are doing it
in their basements back home.

128
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:42,790
Wanna try it?

129
00:15:43,659 --> 00:15:45,593
Come on, Baby.

130
00:16:22,564 --> 00:16:25,692
Can you imagine dancing like this
on the main floor...

131
00:16:25,768 --> 00:16:28,168
home of the family fox-trot?

132
00:16:28,237 --> 00:16:30,762
Max would close
the place down first.

133
00:17:02,905 --> 00:17:05,203
That's my cousin, Johnny Castle.

134
00:17:06,008 --> 00:17:08,306
He got me the job here.

135
00:17:27,329 --> 00:17:29,820
- They look great together.
- Yeah.

136
00:17:29,898 --> 00:17:32,332
You'd think they were
a couple, wouldn't you?

137
00:17:32,401 --> 00:17:36,167
- Aren't they?
- No, not since we were kids.

138
00:18:15,878 --> 00:18:15,944
Do you love me?

139
00:18:15,944 --> 00:18:17,809
Do you love me?

140
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:40,400
Yo, cousin, what's she doing here?

141
00:18:41,069 --> 00:18:43,731
She came with me.
She's with me.

142
00:18:43,806 --> 00:18:45,637
I carried a watermelon.

143
00:18:51,647 --> 00:18:53,740
I carried a watermelon?

144
00:19:27,482 --> 00:19:29,643
Bend your knees. Down.

145
00:19:34,323 --> 00:19:35,847
Watch. Watch my eyes.

146
00:19:36,859 --> 00:19:38,417
Good.

147
00:19:42,564 --> 00:19:44,122
That's better.

148
00:19:49,004 --> 00:19:50,938
Good. Now roll this way.

149
00:19:52,841 --> 00:19:54,468
Now watch.

150
00:20:04,453 --> 00:20:06,148
Look.

151
00:20:16,932 --> 00:20:18,695
Love man!

152
00:20:54,369 --> 00:20:57,827
Ladies, join our hair-raising
wig show.

153
00:20:57,906 --> 00:20:59,874
Try your Sandra Dee,
Jackie Kennedy...

154
00:20:59,942 --> 00:21:02,638
or Elizabeth Taylor-Cleopatra wig.

155
00:21:02,711 --> 00:21:06,203
- I'll knock with three.
- Look at that cute fella.

156
00:21:06,281 --> 00:21:08,545
Look at these hands.
They're golden hands.

157
00:21:11,253 --> 00:21:14,222
My God, it's Cleopatra!
I feel like such an ""asp"".

158
00:21:14,289 --> 00:21:16,553
You look ten years younger.

159
00:21:16,625 --> 00:21:19,526
At 10:.15, by the pool,
we have calisthenics.

160
00:21:19,594 --> 00:21:22,893
Then on the west porch, we have
a symposium by Rabbi Maurice Sherman...

161
00:21:22,965 --> 00:21:25,900
on the psychology
of insult comedians.

162
00:21:27,636 --> 00:21:30,628
So I say, ""Ask not what your waiter
can do for you...

163
00:21:30,706 --> 00:21:33,197
but what you can do
for your waiter.""

164
00:21:33,275 --> 00:21:36,244
If tips keep up, I'll have enough
for my Alfa Romeo.

165
00:21:37,646 --> 00:21:39,477
That's my favorite car.

166
00:21:41,650 --> 00:21:43,914
Ladies, you look very lovely.

167
00:21:44,987 --> 00:21:48,855
Baby, would you cover for me tonight?
Tell Mom and Dad I went to lie down.

168
00:21:48,924 --> 00:21:50,721
Where are you going?

169
00:21:50,792 --> 00:21:54,751
To the golf course. There's
a pretty view from the first tee.

170
00:21:57,966 --> 00:22:00,298
Good. Thanks.

171
00:22:07,409 --> 00:22:10,606
So you were really a Rockette?

172
00:22:10,679 --> 00:22:12,738
I think you're a wonderful dancer.

173
00:22:12,814 --> 00:22:16,215
Yeah? Well, my mother kicked me out
when I was 16.

174
00:22:16,284 --> 00:22:19,947
I've been dancing ever since. It's the
only thing I ever wanted to do anyway.

175
00:22:21,323 --> 00:22:23,257
I envy you.

176
00:22:47,115 --> 00:22:51,142
- Aren't you dancing, Doc?
- We're waiting for a waltz.

177
00:22:52,687 --> 00:22:56,714
Hi, Max. Aren't my dance lessons
starting to pay off?

178
00:22:56,792 --> 00:23:00,284
You look great, Vivian!
Terrific!

179
00:23:03,532 --> 00:23:07,434
That's Vivian Pressman,
one of the bungalow bunnies.

180
00:23:09,137 --> 00:23:12,072
That's what we call the women
who stay here all week.

181
00:23:12,908 --> 00:23:15,843
The husbands only come up
on weekends.

182
00:23:15,911 --> 00:23:19,278
Moe Pressman's a big card player.
He'll join our game.

183
00:23:20,882 --> 00:23:23,680
- Moe coming up on Friday?
- Friday.

184
00:23:24,653 --> 00:23:27,019
He's away a lot. I know.

185
00:23:28,290 --> 00:23:30,315
It's a hardship.

186
00:23:36,431 --> 00:23:40,026
Where's Penny?
Everybody's been asking for her.

187
00:23:41,503 --> 00:23:45,439
What do you mean, where's Penny?
She's taking a break.

188
00:23:45,507 --> 00:23:48,032
As long as it's not
an all-night break.

189
00:23:52,180 --> 00:23:54,705
Come on, doll. Let's take a walk.

190
00:24:04,159 --> 00:24:07,560
I love to watch your hair
blowing in the breeze.

191
00:24:11,166 --> 00:24:13,396
Maybe my parents
are looking for me.

192
00:24:13,468 --> 00:24:15,231
Baby, don't worry.

193
00:24:15,303 --> 00:24:19,069
If they think you're with me, they'll be
the happiest parents at Kellerman's.

194
00:24:21,276 --> 00:24:23,210
I have to say it.

195
00:24:23,278 --> 00:24:26,270
- I'm known as the catch of the county.
- I'm sure you are.

196
00:24:26,348 --> 00:24:29,476
Last week I took a girl away
from Jamie, the lifeguard.

197
00:24:29,551 --> 00:24:34,716
And he said to her,
""What does he have that I don't have?""

198
00:24:34,789 --> 00:24:38,088
And she said, ""Two hotels.""

199
00:24:40,128 --> 00:24:41,254
Robbie.

200
00:24:42,164 --> 00:24:44,189
I don't hear an apology.

201
00:24:44,266 --> 00:24:49,465
Go back to Mommy and Daddy and listen.
Maybe you'll hear one in your dreams.

202
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:54,438
I'm sorry you had
to see that, Baby.

203
00:24:55,343 --> 00:24:57,834
Sometimes in this world...

204
00:24:57,913 --> 00:25:00,438
you see things
you don't wanna see.

205
00:25:05,020 --> 00:25:06,954
You hungry?

206
00:25:07,822 --> 00:25:09,449
Come on.

207
00:25:15,530 --> 00:25:19,466
So, Baby, what do you want?
You can have anything you want.

208
00:25:20,669 --> 00:25:23,263
A brownie, some milk...

209
00:25:23,338 --> 00:25:26,865
Ieftover rice pudding,
beets...

210
00:25:26,942 --> 00:25:28,637
cabbage roll...

211
00:25:32,847 --> 00:25:35,179
fruit salad, sweet gherkins?

212
00:25:35,250 --> 00:25:39,346
Neil, look, I'm sorry.
I better go check on Lisa.

213
00:25:39,421 --> 00:25:41,150
Yeah.

214
00:26:10,919 --> 00:26:13,888
- Why's she here?
- In case Neil comes back.

215
00:26:13,955 --> 00:26:16,048
Penny just doesn't think.

216
00:26:16,124 --> 00:26:19,059
She wouldn't do anything
stupid, would she?

217
00:26:19,928 --> 00:26:23,625
So, what's wrong?
What's the matter with her?

218
00:26:24,666 --> 00:26:27,191
- She's knocked up, Baby.
- Billy!

219
00:26:28,870 --> 00:26:32,863
- What's he gonna do about it?
- ""What's he gonna do about it?""

220
00:26:33,608 --> 00:26:35,166
It's mine, right?

221
00:26:35,243 --> 00:26:37,939
- Right away you think it's mine.
- But I thought...

222
00:26:55,563 --> 00:26:58,225
It's okay. Johnny's here.

223
00:27:02,771 --> 00:27:05,239
I'm never gonna let anything
happen to you.

224
00:27:09,511 --> 00:27:11,445
We got to go.

225
00:27:13,548 --> 00:27:15,914
Just hold on. Just hold on.

226
00:27:15,984 --> 00:27:18,578
Good girl. Good girl.

227
00:27:23,191 --> 00:27:26,183
What do you think you're doing?
You're in trouble, you talk to me.

228
00:27:26,261 --> 00:27:28,695
I'll take care of it.

229
00:27:28,763 --> 00:27:32,290
You should've come to me
in the first place.

230
00:27:32,367 --> 00:27:35,734
Forget it, Johnny. I'm not taking
what's left of your salary.

231
00:27:35,804 --> 00:27:39,763
- Penny, that's my business.
- Besides, it wouldn't be enough.

232
00:27:49,584 --> 00:27:52,018
Oh, God, it's hopeless!

233
00:27:52,087 --> 00:27:54,248
Don't say that.

234
00:27:54,322 --> 00:27:57,291
There's gotta be a way
to work it out.

235
00:27:59,894 --> 00:28:03,295
Baby? Is that your name?

236
00:28:04,199 --> 00:28:05,928
You know what, Baby?

237
00:28:07,001 --> 00:28:09,435
You don't know shit
about my problems.

238
00:28:10,638 --> 00:28:12,629
I told her.

239
00:28:12,707 --> 00:28:18,168
Jesus! She's gonna tell her management
boyfriend and then we'll all get fired.

240
00:28:18,246 --> 00:28:22,546
Why not skywrite it? ""Penny got
knocked up by Robbie, the creep.""

241
00:28:22,617 --> 00:28:25,245
- Look--
- No, Baby.

242
00:28:26,454 --> 00:28:29,321
One of the counselors
