00:59:35,154 --> 00:59:38,590
Auditions for the annual Kellerman
end-of-the-season talent show...

488
00:59:38,658 --> 00:59:40,683
beginning in the playhouse.

489
00:59:47,500 --> 00:59:50,333
- Everyone gonna be in the show?
- We're leaving tomorrow.

490
00:59:50,403 --> 00:59:52,564
Miss the weekend traffic.

491
00:59:52,639 --> 00:59:54,504
But we're paid up 'til Sunday.

492
00:59:54,574 --> 00:59:57,566
- And miss the show?
- I said we're leaving tomorrow.

493
00:59:57,644 --> 01:00:00,636
- I was going to sing in the show.
- It's the big event.

494
01:00:00,713 --> 01:00:03,079
People bring their own arrangements.
You don't want to miss it.

495
01:00:03,149 --> 01:00:05,174
Baby, I need you for props.

496
01:00:06,686 --> 01:00:09,849
Why would you want to leave early?

497
01:00:16,829 --> 01:00:19,662
It was just an idea.
We can stay if you want to.

498
01:00:23,403 --> 01:00:26,930
- So, what were you planning to sing?
- ""l Feel Pretty.""

499
01:00:27,006 --> 01:00:29,998
Or ""What Do the Simple Folk Do?""

500
01:00:30,076 --> 01:00:33,842
Or ""l Feel Pretty.""
What do you think, Daddy?

501
01:00:45,858 --> 01:00:47,291
You look much better.

502
01:00:49,996 --> 01:00:53,557
You just missed your father.
He's such a wonderful man.

503
01:00:55,401 --> 01:00:57,961
I'm sorry. I didn't realize--

504
01:00:58,037 --> 01:01:00,369
You couldn't have. It's okay.

505
01:01:12,385 --> 01:01:15,183
- So, how you doin'?
- I'm okay.

506
01:01:16,789 --> 01:01:19,223
Dr. Houseman says
I'm going to be fine.

507
01:01:20,560 --> 01:01:24,360
- I can still have children.
- Oh, Penny, that's really great.

508
01:01:26,933 --> 01:01:29,697
So, how did it go last night?

509
01:01:29,769 --> 01:01:31,737
Good.

510
01:01:33,039 --> 01:01:37,533
Fine. I didn't do the lifts,
but it was good.

511
01:01:48,254 --> 01:01:52,953
Well, I guess I gonna go.

512
01:01:55,128 --> 01:01:56,755
See ya.

513
01:02:04,837 --> 01:02:07,169
- So, he says you're going to be fine?
- What are you doing?

514
01:02:07,240 --> 01:02:10,698
- I'll tell Max your grandmother died.
- How many times have you told me...

515
01:02:10,777 --> 01:02:13,541
never get mixed-up with them?

516
01:02:13,613 --> 01:02:15,547
I know what I'm doing.

517
01:02:16,616 --> 01:02:20,382
You listen to me.
You've got to stop it now.

518
01:02:36,335 --> 01:02:39,566
Look, I gotta run.
I got a lesson with the Kramers.

519
01:02:39,639 --> 01:02:42,005
They'll kill each other
if I'm not there.

520
01:02:42,074 --> 01:02:44,508
Well, sure. You've gotta go.

521
01:02:47,313 --> 01:02:48,746
I'll see ya.

522
01:03:08,267 --> 01:03:11,168
It's rainy day game time.
Pin the tail on the guest.

523
01:03:11,237 --> 01:03:13,671
Win ten boxes of Kleenex
or a billy goat!

524
01:03:14,740 --> 01:03:18,232
God, I am so sick of this rain.

525
01:03:18,311 --> 01:03:21,007
Remind me not to take my honeymoon
at Niagara Falls.

526
01:03:21,080 --> 01:03:24,208
So, you go to Acapulco.
It'll be fine.

527
01:03:24,283 --> 01:03:27,946
Where is my beige
iridescent lipstick?

528
01:03:28,020 --> 01:03:30,181
I know I put it in this drawer.

529
01:03:30,256 --> 01:03:32,486
Baby, where are you going
in this weather?

530
01:03:32,558 --> 01:03:35,152
Uh, they're having charades
in the west lobby.

531
01:03:35,228 --> 01:03:38,163
Quite the little joiner,
aren't we?

532
01:03:52,945 --> 01:03:56,312
- Have you had many women?
- What?

533
01:03:59,085 --> 01:04:00,916
Baby, come on.

534
01:04:00,987 --> 01:04:02,921
Tell me. I want to know.

535
01:04:14,734 --> 01:04:16,861
You gotta understand
what it's like.

536
01:04:16,936 --> 01:04:19,370
You come from the streets
and suddenly you're up here.

537
01:04:19,438 --> 01:04:23,340
Women are throwing themselves
at you and they smell so good.

538
01:04:23,409 --> 01:04:25,502
They really take care
of themselves.

539
01:04:25,578 --> 01:04:28,012
I never knew women
could be like that.

540
01:04:28,080 --> 01:04:31,345
They're so goddamn rich you think
they must know about everything.

541
01:04:31,417 --> 01:04:34,113
They're slippin' their room keys
in my hand two and three times a day--

542
01:04:34,186 --> 01:04:38,384
different women--
so, I think I'm scorin' big, right?

543
01:04:38,457 --> 01:04:42,894
You think, ""They wouldn't be doing this
if they didn't care about me, right?""

544
01:04:44,096 --> 01:04:47,065
That's all right. I understand.
You were just using them, that's all.

545
01:04:49,001 --> 01:04:50,468
No, that's not it.

546
01:04:51,404 --> 01:04:53,702
That's the thing.
It wasn't like that.

547
01:04:55,808 --> 01:04:57,901
They were using me.

548
01:05:25,471 --> 01:05:27,405
What's your real name, Baby?

549
01:05:29,375 --> 01:05:33,573
Frances, for the first woman
in the Cabinet.

550
01:05:35,781 --> 01:05:39,148
Frances.
That's a real grownup name.

551
01:05:52,331 --> 01:05:54,765
I've decided to go
all the way with Robbie.

552
01:05:57,336 --> 01:06:01,033
No, not with someone like him.

553
01:06:01,107 --> 01:06:05,476
Do you think if we came back for a
ten-year anniversary, it would be free?

554
01:06:05,544 --> 01:06:09,071
It's just wrong this way.
It should be with someone--

555
01:06:09,148 --> 01:06:13,710
With someone that
you sort of love.

556
01:06:13,786 --> 01:06:18,018
Come on.
You don't care about me.

557
01:06:18,090 --> 01:06:21,116
You wouldn't care if I humped
the entire army...

558
01:06:21,193 --> 01:06:24,356
as long as we were on the right side
of the Ho Chi Minh Trail.

559
01:06:24,430 --> 01:06:29,265
What you care about is that
you're not Daddy's girl anymore.

560
01:06:29,335 --> 01:06:31,769
He listens when I talk now.

561
01:06:32,905 --> 01:06:34,338
You hate that.

562
01:06:51,524 --> 01:06:54,288
Two, three, cha-cha-cha.

563
01:06:54,360 --> 01:06:57,227
My frame.
Where's my pleasing arc?

564
01:06:57,296 --> 01:07:00,857
Spaghetti arms! Would you
give me some tension, please?

565
01:07:02,735 --> 01:07:06,102
You're invading my dance space.
This is my dance space.

566
01:07:06,172 --> 01:07:08,572
That's yours. Let's cha-cha.

567
01:07:14,747 --> 01:07:17,409
Don't look down.
Look right here.

568
01:07:26,325 --> 01:07:31,092
- How you call your lover boy?
- Come here, lover boy.

569
01:07:31,163 --> 01:07:34,724
- And if he doesn't answer?
- Oh, lover boy.

570
01:07:34,800 --> 01:07:38,167
- And if still doesn't answer?
- I simply say...

571
01:07:38,237 --> 01:07:41,001
Baby

572
01:07:41,073 --> 01:07:43,906
O-Oh, baby

573
01:07:44,977 --> 01:07:47,810
My sweet baby

574
01:07:48,881 --> 01:07:50,815
You're the one

575
01:08:06,165 --> 01:08:07,655
Takin' dance lessons?

576
01:08:08,734 --> 01:08:10,668
I could teach ya, kid.

577
01:08:15,374 --> 01:08:18,366
My grandfather put me in charge
of the final show.

578
01:08:18,444 --> 01:08:20,742
I want to talk to you
about the last dance.

579
01:08:20,813 --> 01:08:23,907
I'd like to shake things up a bit.

580
01:08:23,983 --> 01:08:26,611
You know, move with the times.

581
01:08:26,685 --> 01:08:28,710
I've got a lot of ideas.

582
01:08:28,788 --> 01:08:30,847
I've been working
with the staff kids...

583
01:08:30,923 --> 01:08:34,450
on a cross between a Cuban rhythm
and soul dancing.

584
01:08:34,527 --> 01:08:37,325
Whoa, boy.

585
01:08:37,396 --> 01:08:39,660
Way over your head here.

586
01:08:39,732 --> 01:08:43,725
You always do the mambo, huh?

587
01:08:43,803 --> 01:08:47,000
Why not dance this year's
final dance...

588
01:08:49,041 --> 01:08:50,906
to the pachenga?

589
01:08:52,111 --> 01:08:53,237
Right.

590
01:08:55,414 --> 01:08:59,145
Well, you're free to do the same,
tired number as last year if you want...

591
01:08:59,218 --> 01:09:02,153
but next year we'll find
another dance person...

592
01:09:02,221 --> 01:09:04,621
- who'll only be too happy--
- Sure, Neil. No problem.

593
01:09:06,826 --> 01:09:08,987
We'll end the season
with the pachenga.

594
01:09:09,061 --> 01:09:10,528
Great idea.

595
01:09:17,069 --> 01:09:21,438
Sometimes he's hard to talk to,
but the ladies seem to like him.

596
01:09:21,507 --> 01:09:24,499
See that he gives you the full half-hour
you're paying him for, kid.

597
01:09:33,385 --> 01:09:36,445
That little wimp. He wouldn't know a
new idea if it hit him in the pachenga.

598
01:09:36,522 --> 01:09:38,820
I could have told him
some new ideas.

599
01:09:38,891 --> 01:09:40,882
Why did you let him
talk to you that way?

600
01:09:40,960 --> 01:09:43,451
- What, fight the boss man?
- You tell him your ideas.

601
01:09:43,529 --> 01:09:46,327
- He's a person like everyone else.
- Look, I know these people.

602
01:09:46,398 --> 01:09:49,060
They are rich and they're mean.
They won't listen to me.

603
01:09:49,134 --> 01:09:51,568
Why not fight harder?
Make them listen.

604
01:09:51,637 --> 01:09:54,538
Because I need this goddamned job
lined up for next summer.

605
01:09:55,608 --> 01:09:57,701
My dad calls me today.

606
01:09:57,776 --> 01:10:00,404
""Good news,"" he says. ""Uncle Paul
can finally get you in the union.""

607
01:10:00,479 --> 01:10:01,741
What union?

608
01:10:02,915 --> 01:10:06,851
The House Painters and Plasterers
Local Number 179 at your service.

609
01:10:14,960 --> 01:10:17,520
I've been thinking a lot
about the Domino Theory.

610
01:10:17,596 --> 01:10:19,928
Now, when Viet Nam falls,
is China Next?

611
01:10:22,768 --> 01:10:24,702
I don't think they saw us.

612
01:10:35,881 --> 01:10:37,314
Fight harder, huh?

613
01:10:38,384 --> 01:10:42,115
I don't see you fightin' so hard,
tellin' Daddy I'm your guy.

614
01:10:42,187 --> 01:10:44,382
I will. With my father,
it's complicated.

615
01:10:44,456 --> 01:10:46,890
- I will tell him.
- I don't believe you, Baby.

616
01:10:50,562 --> 01:10:51,995
I don't think...

617
01:10:53,532 --> 01:10:56,296
that you ever had
any intention of telling him.

618
01:10:57,369 --> 01:10:58,495
Ever.

619
01:11:09,548 --> 01:11:09,581
Well, Cousin, it's almost over.
Labor Day weekend is here.

620
01:11:09,581 --> 01:11:12,379
Well, Cousin, it's almost over.
Labor Day weekend is here.

621
01:11:12,451 --> 01:11:16,148
Soon it's back to the old books and
back to work. What a terrible thought!

622
01:11:25,931 --> 01:11:27,865
Have you seen Johnny?

623
01:11:43,682 --> 01:11:44,944
I'm sorry.

624
01:11:49,388 --> 01:11:51,322
Looks like I picked
the wrong sister.

625
01:11:51,390 --> 01:11:54,188
That's okay, Baby.
I went slummin' too.

626
01:12:12,044 --> 01:12:13,705
Hit me.

627
01:12:20,819 --> 01:12:22,753
Get out of here.
You're not worth it.

628
01:13:20,946 --> 01:13:23,141
Win big, Moe.

629
01:13:23,215 --> 01:13:24,477
As always.

630
01:13:42,034 --> 01:13:45,868
This is our last night together, lover.
I've got something worked out for us.

631
01:14:08,527 --> 01:14:10,825
Excuse me, sir.
The pirate number's next.

632
01:14:10,896 --> 01:14:13,194
Oh, thanks.
Hey, kid.

633
01:14:13,265 --> 01:14:15,995
I've been playing cards all weekend
and I've got an all-night game tonight.

634
01:14:16,068 --> 01:14:19,595
Why don't you give my wife
some extra dance lessons?

635
01:14:28,614 --> 01:14:30,548
I'm sorry, Mr. Pressman...

636
01:14:30,616 --> 01:14:33,141
but I'm booked up for
the whole weekend with the show.

637
01:14:33,218 --> 01:14:35,413
I won't have time
for anything else.

638
01:14:35,487 --> 01:14:38,684
I don't think it'd be fair
to take the money.

639
01:15:03,448 --> 01:15:06,281
I've decided tonight's the night
with Robbie.

640
01:15:06,351 --> 01:15:08,512
He doesn't even know yet.

641
01:15:44,189 --> 01:15:45,451
It's me.

642
01:15:50,629 --> 01:15:51,960
Holy shit!

643
01:16:13,018 --> 01:16:15,111
You wanna hear somethin' crazy?

644
01:16:19,458 --> 01:16:20,891
Last night l--

645
01:16:22,094 --> 01:16:26,360
I dreamt we were walking along
and we met your father.

646
01:16:26,431 --> 01:16:29,093
He said, ""Come on,""
and he put his arm around me.

647
01:16:30,802 --> 01:16:32,895
Just like he did with Robbie.

648
01:17:20,185 --> 01:17:25,452
You know how you feel when you see a
patient and you think he's all right...

649
01:17:25,524 --> 01:17:28,459
then you look at the X rays
and it's nothing like you thought?

650
01:17:28,527 --> 01:17:29,789
What happened?

651
01:17:29,861 --> 01:17:33,297
It's exactly what it's like when you
find out one of your staff's a thief.

652
01:17:33,365 --> 01:17:37,028
Moe Pressman's wallet was stolen
when he was playing pinochle last night.

653
01:17:37,102 --> 01:17:40,128
It was in his jacket hanging
on the back of his chair.

654
01:17:40,205 --> 01:17:44,437
He had it at 1:30 and when he
checked again at quarter of 4::00...

655
01:17:44,509 --> 01:17:46,909
it was missing.

656
01:17:46,978 --> 01:17:51,506
Vivian thinks she remembers
this dance kid Johnny...

657
01:17:51,583 --> 01:17:52,845
walking by.

658
01:17:53,919 --> 01:17:57,787
So we ask him,
""You have an alibi for last night?""

659
01:17:57,856 --> 01:18:00,086
He says he was alone
in his room reading.

660
01:18:01,460 --> 01:18:03,894
There are no books
in Johnny's room!

661
01:18:05,864 --> 01:18:07,923
There's been a mistake.
I know Johnny didn't do it.

662
01:18:07,999 --> 01:18:10,467
There's been similar thefts at the
Sheldrake. It's happened here before.

663
01:18:10,535 --> 01:18:12,901
- Three other wallets.
- I know he didn't do it.

664
01:18:12,971 --> 01:18:15,064
Stay out of it, Baby.

665
01:18:15,140 --> 01:18:18,974
Wait. Don't put those
tables together. Come on.

666
01:18:21,246 --> 01:18:25,307
Daddy, I need your help.
I know Johnny didn't take Moe's wallet.

667
01:18:25,384 --> 01:18:27,750
- Oh? How do you know?
- I can't tell you.

668
01:18:27,819 --> 01:18:32,620
- Just please trust me, Daddy.
- I'm sorry, Baby. I can't.

669
01:18:32,691 --> 01:18:34,784
This Danish is pure protein.

670
01:18:37,629 --> 01:18:41,326
Maybe Johnny didn't do it.
Anyone could've taken it.

671
01:18:41,400 --> 01:18:43,334
Maybe it was, uh--

672
01:18:43,402 --> 01:18:46,269
It could've been that little,
old couple, the Schumachers.

673
01:18:46,338 --> 01:18:49,569
- I saw her with a couple of wallets.
- Sylvia and Sidney?

674
01:18:49,641 --> 01:18:52,701
Baby, you don't go around
accusing innocent people.

675
01:18:52,778 --> 01:18:57,238
I even saw them at the Sheldrake. You
said something was stolen from there.

676
01:18:57,315 --> 01:19:00,910
I got an eyewitness
and the kid has no alibi.

677
01:19:00,986 --> 01:19:04,888
Come on, Neil. You'll learn
what it's like to fire an employee.

678
01:19:06,124 --> 01:19:09,616
Wait a minute. I know Johnny
didn't take the wallet.

679
01:19:09,694 --> 01:19:12,925
I know because he was
in his room all night.

680
01:19:12,998 --> 01:19:17,458
And the reason I know
is because I was with him.

681
01:19:41,860 --> 01:19:43,794
I told you I was
telling the truth.

682
01:19:48,667 --> 01:19:50,601
I'm sorry I lied to you.

683
01:19:53,505 --> 01:19:55,439
But you lied too.

684
01:19:57,676 --> 01:20:01,203
You told me everyone was alike
and deserved a fair break.

685
01:20:01,279 --> 01:20:03,372
But you meant everyone
who is like you.

686
01:20:06,151 --> 01:20:09,382
You told me you wanted me to change
the world, to make it better.

687
01:20:10,455 --> 01:20:13,083
But you meant by becoming
a lawyer or an economist...

688
01:20:13,158 --> 01:20:15,319
and marrying someone
from Harvard.

689
01:20:17,996 --> 01:20:20,521
I'm not proud of myself.

690
01:20:20,599 --> 01:20:24,126
But I'm in this family too. You can't
keep giving me the silent treatment.

691
01:20:27,672 --> 01:20:30,470
There are a lot of things about me
that aren't what you thought.

692
01:20:31,543 --> 01:20:34,478
But if you love me, you have to love
all the things about me.

693
01:20:37,148 --> 01:20:39,082
And I love you.

694
01:20:39,150 --> 01:20:43,746
I'm sorry I let you down.
I'm so sorry, Daddy.

695
01:20:44,623 --> 01:20:46,887
But you let me down too.

696
01:21:17,155 --> 01:21:19,385
I have been lookin'
for you all over.

697
01:21:20,358 --> 01:21:22,223
They found the Schumachers.

698
01:21:22,294 --> 01:21:24,626
Fingerprinted their water glasses.

699
01:21:24,696 --> 01:21:27,563
Found out they were wanted
in Arizona and in Florida...

700
01:21:27,632 --> 01:21:30,032
and they made a fortune
here this summer.

701
01:21:30,101 --> 01:21:32,035
So then it's all right.

702
01:21:33,171 --> 01:21:35,196
I knew it would work out.

703
01:21:35,273 --> 01:21:37,537
- I knew they'd have to apologize.
- I'm out, Baby.

704
01:21:42,814 --> 01:21:44,748
They fired you anyway
because of me.

705
01:21:46,384 --> 01:21:49,751
And if I leave quietly,
I'll get my summer bonus.

706
01:21:52,724 --> 01:21:54,658
So I did it for nothing.

707
01:21:54,726 --> 01:21:58,753
I hurt my family, you lost your job
anyway-- I did it for nothing!

708
01:21:58,830 --> 01:22:00,764
No, not for nothing.

709
01:22:00,832 --> 01:22:04,165
Nobody has ever done anything
like that for me before.

710
01:22:04,970 --> 01:22:08,167
You were right. You can't win
no matter what you do.

711
01:22:08,239 --> 01:22:11,697
Listen to me. I don't want
to hear that from you. You can.

712
01:22:13,645 --> 01:22:15,738
I used to think so.

713
01:22:37,335 --> 01:22:39,428
Dr. Houseman, can l, uh--

714
01:22:40,905 --> 01:22:43,965
Look, I'm going anyway and I know
what you must be thinking.

715
01:22:44,042 --> 01:22:47,011
You don't know
anything at all about me.

716
01:22:47,078 --> 01:22:49,774
I know you want Baby
to be like you.

717
01:22:49,848 --> 01:22:52,681
The kind of person
people look up to.

718
01:22:52,751 --> 01:22:54,946
Baby is like that.
If you could just see--

719
01:22:55,020 --> 01:22:57,955
Don't you tell me what to see.

720
01:22:58,023 --> 01:23:00,617
I see someone in front of me
who got his partner in trouble...

721
01:23:00,692 --> 01:23:03,058
and sent her off
to some butcher...

722
01:23:03,128 --> 01:23:06,393
while he moved on to an innocent,
young girl like my daughter.

